ny from the private correspondence she sent him directly."},{"number":2,"category":"literature","header":"Eleven-year breach repaired at her father's funeral","body":"She and Bowles had a falling-out in 1863 that lasted eleven years, despite his continued visits to her brother Austin next door at The Evergreens. The breach ended when her father Edward died in 1874 — Bowles was the only non-family member she spoke to at the funeral, and she wrote thanking him for his kindness shortly after."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"Mourned Bowles two years before her own death","body":"Bowles died in January 1878; she wrote to his widow Mary, 'Dear Mr Sam is very near, these midwinter days. When purples come on Pelham, in the afternoon we say Mr Bowles's colors.' She herself died eight years later in May 1886."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"emily-dickinson-x02563"},"H02158":{"id":"H02158","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Beulah","middle_name":"Maria","last_name":"Whitford","maiden_name":"Murray","married_names":["Whitford"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Beulah Maria Murray Whitford"},"birth":{"year":1810,"month":12,"day":28,"city":"East Guilford","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1864,"month":4,"day":10,"country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":7,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"X02455","mother_id":"H01044"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02564","date_year":1839,"date_month":1,"d